        "cases/transient-profile-load/verifier/profile-loader.hidden.mjs"
      ],
      "task": "Users report that after a profile load fails once, later requests for the same profile can keep returning that first error even after the upstream service has recovered. Before editing, run the included `node repro/transient-profile-load.mjs`; use its structured output to trace the first incorrect transition. Fix the root cause while preserving the `createProfileLoader` API, loader error propagation, fulfilled-result reuse, overlapping same-profile single-flight behavior, and independence between profile IDs; keep `createProfileLoader` as a direct named export. Add focused regressions for four independent sequences: complete a rejected request and then start a same-ID retry that makes a fresh loader call and succeeds; start two same-ID requests before allowing the loader to settle and prove only one loader call occurs; complete a successful request and then prove a later same-ID request reuses it; cache a success for one ID, fail another ID, and prove the first remains cached. Run the full test suite. Do not commit, install packages, use the network, or create another worktree.",
